	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Three firefighters have died after battling a blaze in a building belonging to the Gauteng government. Gauteng MEC for Infrastructure Development Jacob Mamabolo confirmed the deaths at a media briefing on Wednesday afternoon. Two firefighters are believed to have succumbed to their injuries after they became trapped in the building. The third fell to his death while battling the blaze. (see picture below. Warning: Not for sensitive viewers) READ: Firefighter dies after falling from upper floors of burning Joburg building Thirteen people were taken to hospital for treatment. The fire, which was allegedly caused by an electrical fault, broke out on the 23rd floor of the building, which is shared by the departments of health, human settlements and co-operative governance. All workers were evacuated from the building. Mamabolo said everyone would stay home until they could be relocated. "The building does not comply with occupational health and safety, was not compliant with the basic regulations," he told the briefing.      24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  